{"questionId":"33231019","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The time worked, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>, in hours per week by employees of a large company is normally&nbsp;distributed with a mean of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>42</mn></math> and standard deviation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A large group of employees work more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn></math> hours per week.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>An employee is selected at random from this large group.</p>\n<p>Find the probability that this employee works less than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>55</mn></math> hours per week.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not penalize for inclusion or non-inclusion of endpoints for probabilities using a normal distribution. For example, for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>55</mn><mo> </mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>40</mn></menclose></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>55</mn><mo> </mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>40</mn></menclose></mrow></mfenced></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>55</mn><mo> </mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>T</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>40</mn></menclose></mrow></mfenced></math>, etc.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>recognizing conditional probability&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>55</mn><mo> </mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>40</mn></menclose></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for an expression or description in context. Accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>40</mn><mo> </mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>55</mn></menclose></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;but do not accept just&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo> </mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>B</mi></menclose></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mn>40</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>55</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>40</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>461944</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>574136</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>55</mn><mo> </mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>40</mn></menclose></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>804590</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>805</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33231019","referenceCo